{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox journal | title = Communication Studies | cover = 2018 Comm Stud cover.jpg | editor = Patric R. Spence | discipline = [[Communication studies]] | former_names = Central States Speech Journal | abbreviation = Commun. Stud. | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = | frequency = 5/year | history = 1949-present | openaccess = [[Hybrid_open-access_journal|Hybrid]] | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = https://www.tandfonline.com/action/journalInformation?journalCode=rcst20 | link1 = https://www.tandfonline.com/toc/rcst20/current?nav=tocList | link1-name = Online access | link2 = https://www.tandfonline.com/loi/rcst20 | link2-name = Online archive | link3 = https://www.csca-net.org/aws/CSCA/pt/sp/publications_communication_studies | link3-name = Journal page at association's website | JSTOR = | OCLC = 1039363909 | LCCN = 56046080 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1051-0974 | eISSN = 1745-1035 }} '''''Communication Studies''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers communication processes, specifically [[communication theory]] and research. It was established in 1949 as the '''''Central States Speech Journal''''', obtaining its current title in 1989. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Patric R. Spence ([[University of Central Florida]]). It is published in 5 issues a year by [[Routledge]] and is an official journal of the [[Central States Communication Association]].
According to data published in ''[[Scientometrics (journal)|Scientometrics]]'' ''Communication Studies'' was rated as the fifth-most central journal to the field of human communication.<ref>{{cite journal |last1=Griffin |first1=Darrin J |last2=Bolkan |first2=San |last3=Holmgrem |first3=Jennifer |last4=Tutzauer |first4=Frank |title=Central journals and authors in communication using a publication network|journal=Scientometrics|date=January 2016 |volume=106 |issue=1 |pages=91–104 |doi=10.1007/s11192-015-1774-4}}</ref>
