'''Somatic effort''' refers to the total investments of an [[organism]] in its own [[developmental biology|development]], [[Cellular differentiation|differentiation]], and [[Maintenance of an organism|maintenance]] which consequently increases its [[Biological reproduction|reproductive]] potential.<ref>[https://books.google.com.au/books?id=ktk-49WsoscC&lpg=PA293&ots=fJeHm0BGIw&dq=%22Somatic%20effort%22%20-wikipedia&pg=PA293#v=onepage&q=%22Somatic%20effort%22%20-wikipedia&f=false Page 293], Evolution and Literary Theory, By Joseph Carroll, University of Missouri Press, 1995</ref>

